- `TransactionAnalysisParams` interface: { type: "expense" | "income", startDate?: string, endDate?: string, categoryId?: string, subcategoryId?: string, tagIds?: string[], accountId?: string, search?: string, skip?: number, take?: number }
- `TransactionAnalysisBreakdownItem` interface: { id: string, name: string, amount: number, percentage: number }
- `TransactionAnalysisTransaction` interface: { id: string, name: string, amount: number, date: string, categoryName: string, subcategoryName?: string, accountName: string }
- `TransactionAnalysisResponse` interface: { type: "expense" | "income", totalAmount: number, transactionCount: number, breakdown: TransactionAnalysisBreakdownItem[], transactions: TransactionAnalysisTransaction[], hasMore: boolean }

In `src/app/globals.css`:

1. Add a new `.field-reveal` class block in `@layer components` (after `.money-map-card-interactive`):
   ```css
   .field-reveal {
     display: grid;
     grid-template-rows: 0fr;
     transition: grid-template-rows 200ms ease-out;
   }
   .field-reveal[data-visible="true"] {
     grid-template-rows: 1fr;
   }
   .field-reveal > div {
     overflow: hidden;
   }
   ```

2. Add `.field-reveal` to the existing `@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)` block:
   ```css
   .field-reveal {
     transition: none !important;
   }
   ```

This mirrors the existing `.nav-group-content` pattern (lines 237-253).
